column1: Despite decreases in positive mental health and self-efficacy, the substantial reductions in general psychopathology (-0.83), anxiety sensitivity (-0.86), and fear of bodily sensations (-0.85), combined with significantly increased social support (+0.71), strongly indicate movement away from psychological disorder rather than toward it.

Despite concerning increases in anxiety-related measures (fear of bodily sensations, anxiety sensitivity) and decreases in protective factors (positive mental health, social support), the substantial reduction in general psychopathology (-1.09) combined with significant improvement in self-efficacy (+1.75) indicates an overall positive trajectory that likely prevents development of a new psychological disorder.
